{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bf3b939c-e44c-4d73-9ef4-243903dbc103","content":"Yes, you'll hit **target framework compatibility issues** with MSTest v3. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Dropped frameworks in MSTest v3:**\n\n| Target | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ❌ Dropped — minimum is `net462` → actually **net462 is supported**, but only ≥ .NET Framework 4.6.2 |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ **Dropped** — .NET Core 3.1 is no longer supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ **Dropped** — .NET 5 is no longer supported |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2** (you're fine there) and **.NET 6+** for modern TFMs. Both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` need to be updated.\n\n**Recommended fix** — update your `TargetFrameworks` to:\n```\nnet462;net6.0\n```\n(or `net8.0` if you can target the latest LTS).\n\nWould you like me to run the full MSTest v3 migration on this project? It will also handle any API breaking changes (assertion overloads, `DataRow` constructors, timeout behavior, etc.).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9d819030-4516-4197-bb11-348972b099ac","outputTokens":311,"requestId":"1BC2:315D54:A821DD:BE369D:6A03ECD9"},"id":"2bb847e4-7ba2-41b4-8367-a893961af777","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:15:47.946Z","parentId":"bbb459e1-6cbf-4557-bae2-2aeea40754d9"}
